eNCA's Heidi Giokos reported on the affordable house issue in Johannesburg. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - When will the lack of housing for those in need be adequately addressed in the City of Joburg? From land grabs to high-jacked buildings in the CBD, people have been resorting to desperate measures just to find shelter. And every year it seems to be getting worse. READ: Rabie Ridge | The land is not ours - Gauteng govt The Constitution recognises access to adequate housing as a basic human right but in the City of Johannesburg, many people live without it.
The City said the problem is growing with more informal settlements mushrooming and land grabs increasing. * eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports.